other_tests.findings: The appendix is top-normal size to minimally dilated, measuring 6-8 mm in diameter. The appendix does not fill with oral contrast and is fluid-filled. No bowel obstruction is seen. No periappendiceal free fluid or stranding. The visualized lung bases are clear. The liver is homogeneous in texture with no focal lesions. There is no biliary ductal dilatation. The spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys are unremarkable with no contour irregularities or hydronephrosis. The sigmoid colon and rectum are normal in appearance. The bladder is normal.
